"Abstract This article shows that given enough hardware and software, we can protect most systems. However, we must remember that with every level of security we add, we suffer a decrease in the productivity of our users. It can't take them 10 minutes to log on. That is of coutse, unless our organisations are handling classified information. With proper safeguards we can protect against MOST viruses. But as people create anti-virus programs and procedures others will come up with methods to beat them! People are your great asset and they can be your greatest threat in any security plan, be it private industry or military. You can put all the hardware and procedures in place, but if your people don't endorse the security plan yo can be compromised. There are only a few of the things you can do to protect yourself from viruses. Viruses do not magically appear on systems, they are let in! Viruses infect systems only when people let them."
